==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unsheathe
<hw>Un*sheathe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sheath</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of a sheath;
to draw from the sheath or scabbard, as a sword.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To unsheathe the sword</b></col>, <cd>to make
war.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unshed</ent>⟦br⟧
